# Ashish Dhakane — Portfolio

My personal portfolio site — a full-stack developer with a strong interest in cybersecurity, showcasing my projects, experience, skills, and certifications.

**Live site:** [ashishdhakane.dev](https://ashishdhakane.dev) <!-- update if different -->

---

## ✨ Features

- **Interactive 3D hero section** built with Three.js / React Three Fiber
- **Smooth scroll & motion animations** powered by Framer Motion
- **Responsive, dark-themed UI** with a custom neon-cyan / electric-indigo design system
- **Certifications gallery** — click-to-expand modal with a scrollable grid and a full-size lightbox view (prev/next navigation, keyboard controls)
- **Working contact form** that sends real emails via the Resend API
- **SEO-ready** — Open Graph & Twitter card metadata, sitemap, and robots.txt

## 🧱 Sections

| Section | Description |
|---|---|
| Hero | Intro, role, and quick links (GitHub, LinkedIn, email) |
| About | Bio + technical skill matrix (languages, backend, devops, frontend) |
| Experience | Professional work history |
| Projects | Featured projects with tech stack tags |
| Certifications | Gallery of course/hackathon certificates |
| Achievements & Education | Awards, hackathons, and degree info |
| Contact | Contact form + direct contact details |

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- **Framework:** [Next.js 14](https://nextjs.org/) (App Router) + TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **Animation:** Framer Motion
- **3D:** Three.js via `@react-three/fiber` and `@react-three/drei`
- **Smooth scrolling:** Lenis
- **Email:** Resend API
- **Icons:** lucide-react
- **Deployment:** Vercel

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+
- npm

### Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/ashish-dhakane/PORTFOLIO_NEWW.git
cd PORTFOLIO_NEWW
npm install
```

### Environment variables

Copy the example file and fill in your own values:

```bash
cp .env.local.example .env.local
```

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `RESEND_API_KEY` | API key from [resend.com](https://resend.com/api-keys) |
| `FROM_EMAIL` | Sender address (use `onboarding@resend.dev` for testing) |
| `CONTACT_EMAIL` | Where contact-form submissions are delivered |

### Run locally

```bash
npm run dev
```

Visit [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000).

### Other scripts

```bash
npm run build   # production build
npm run start   # run the production build
npm run lint    # lint the project
```

## 📁 Project Structure

```
├── app/                  # Next.js App Router pages, layout, metadata
├── components/
│   ├── sections/         # Hero, About, Experience, Projects, Certifications, Achievements, Footer
│   ├── ui/                # Navbar, GlowCard, SectionHeading, ContactForm, CertificateModal, etc.
│   └── three/             # 3D background components
├── lib/                  # Motion variants, utils, smooth scroll setup
├── public/
│   └── images/
│       └── certificates/  # Certificate images shown in the gallery
└── tailwind.config.ts     # Design tokens (colors, fonts, spacing)
```

## 📦 Deployment

This project is deployed on [Vercel](https://vercel.com/). Pushing to `main` triggers an automatic redeploy. Make sure the environment variables above are also set in your Vercel project settings.

